<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,866,1052]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,946,972]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: This is the only digitiform 
<taxonomicName box="[648,751,946,971]" class="Demospongiae" family="Aplysinidae" genus="Aplysina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Verongida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[648,751,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Aplysina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a surface covered by shallow depressions and having a skeleton made of an orthogonal reticulation of stout spongin fibres. The colour is beige with purple spots 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">in vivo</emphasis>
, turning into purple when preserved in ethanol.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178898/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" targetBox="[287,1299,1104,1930]" targetPageId="38">
