</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,151,418]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,351,191,217]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Distribution</emphasis>
: Provisionally known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[784,834,192,218]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">type</typeStatus>
locality off the State of Bahia (
<collectingCountry box="[1202,1278,192,218]" name="Brazil" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Brazil</collectingCountry>
; 
<figureCitation box="[1290,1376,192,218]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="39.[151,255,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[315,1266,667,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[264,1323,637,1922]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 22: Map showing the distribution of Aplysina along the Brazilian coastline. A. Aplysina orthoreticulata sp. n. B. Aplysina pseudolacunosa sp. n. C. Aplysina solangeae sp. n.. Scale bar = 500 km." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178899/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number box="[1344,1376,192,218]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
A). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,333,231,257]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Etymology</emphasis>
: The specific name 
<taxonomicName box="[571,742,232,258]" class="Demospongiae" family="Aplysinidae" genus="Aplysina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Verongida" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="orthoreticulata">orthoreticulata</taxonomicName>
is derived from the new species’ orthogonal reticulation. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,312,271,297]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[328,615,272,297]" class="Demospongiae" family="Aplysinidae" genus="Aplysina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Verongida" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="orthoreticulata" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis box="[328,615,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Aplysina orthoreticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[623,678,272,298]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
presents a superficial resemblance to 
<taxonomicName box="[1127,1293,272,297]" class="Demospongiae" family="Aplysinidae" genus="Aplysina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Verongida" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="cauliformis">
<emphasis box="[1127,1293,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">A. cauliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. above), both comprising digitiform branches of regular diameter. However, none of the currently recognized morphotypes of the latter (see above) possess their surface excavated by shallow depressions and the orthogonal reticulation, which is unique within the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
